    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix widget child insertion in GUI library\n\n### Summary\nThe GUI widget system in the tracer was not properly maintaining the doubly-linked list structure when inserting child widgets at specific positions. This caused widgets to not display correctly and could lead to crashes when traversing the widget tree.\n\nThe issue occurred because when inserting a new widget between two existing widgets, the new widget's `last` pointer was not being initialized. This broke the invariant that the `last` pointer on the head of the list should always point to the actual last element.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/gui/widget.c`: Added missing `last` pointer initialization in `widget_add_child_internal` when inserting in the middle of a list.\n\n"
}